  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-size cubes, cover in <strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>cashews</strong> roughly then add them to a dry pot (with a matching lid) over a medium-low heat and toast for 1-2 min or until just starting to brown (you will use this pot for your rice)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati&nbsp;rice</strong> to the pot with the <strong>toasted&nbsp;</strong><strong>cashews</strong>, stir and toast for a further 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to very low&nbsp;and cook, covered,&nbsp;for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and dice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced&nbsp;onion</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5&nbsp;min or until the onion has softened slightly, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for a further 2-4 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/665.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;ginger</strong> and <strong>cumin seeds</strong> to the pan&nbsp;and cook for a further 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> ground&nbsp;turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>curry powder,</strong> &nbsp;a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
